@baseUrl = http://localhost:5180

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# FLIGHT
# Typical sequence:
#   1. Power on          (power.http)
#   2. Take off          → TakingOff → Hovering
#   3. Load waypoints    (waypoints.http)
#   4. Navigate          → Flying
#   5. Hover             → Hovering  (pause navigation)
#   6. Land              → Landing → Idle
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Take Off  (default altitude from config: 30 m)
# Requires: Idle state
# Optional body — omit to use the configured default hover altitude
POST {{baseUrl}}/drone/takeoff
Content-Type: application/json

{}

###

### Take Off to specific altitude (metres)
POST {{baseUrl}}/drone/takeoff
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "altitude": 50.0
}

###

### Hover  (pause in place)
# Requires: Flying state
POST {{baseUrl}}/drone/hover

###

### Navigate  (start executing waypoint queue)
# Requires: Hovering state + at least one waypoint loaded
POST {{baseUrl}}/drone/navigate

###

### Set Speed  (cruise speed in m/s)
# Works in any powered-on state; resets to default on power-off
PUT {{baseUrl}}/drone/speed
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "speedMps": 10.0
}

###

### Set Speed  (maximum — 15 m/s)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/drone/speed
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "speedMps": 10.0
}

###

### Adjust Altitude  (mid-flight, metres above ground)
# Requires: Hovering or Flying state; must be > 0 and ≤ configured max altitude
PUT {{baseUrl}}/drone/altitude
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "altitudeMeters": 45.0
}

###

### Adjust Altitude  (low pass — 15 m)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/drone/altitude
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "altitudeMeters": 15.0
}

###

### Land
# Requires: Hovering or Flying state
POST {{baseUrl}}/drone/land

###

### Return Home
# Requires: Hovering or Flying state
# Auto-lands at home position on arrival
POST {{baseUrl}}/drone/return-home

###
